# Phase Loop Dynamics: A Syntax of Drift, Repair, and Resonance

**Author**: Kiyoshi Sasano  
**Version**: Final (2025-08-03)  
**License**: CC-BY 4.0  
**DOI**: [To Be Assigned via Zenodo]  
**Repository**: https://github.com/kiyoshisasano-DeepZenSpace/kiyoshisasano-DeepZenSpace/tree/main

---

## üìñ Summary

Phase Loop Dynamics (PLD) offers a recursive model of syntax where language is modeled not linearly but as looped, adaptive interactions. Drift, repair, latency, and resonance are treated not as errors but as structured features of discourse.

This repository contains the full manuscript (`Phase_Loop_Dynamics__Sasano_2025_FINAL_TEXT_ONLY.pdf`), accompanied by supporting diagrams, simulation data, YAML logs, and mappings in BibTeX, JSON-LD, and RDF.

---

